          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Leu493Argfs*13) in the POLE gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in POLE are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 23230001, 25948378, 30503519). This variant is present in population databases (rs760070332, gnomAD 0.01%). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with POLE-related conditions. ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 473459). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
