          <Comment>The c.1478delT variant, located in coding exon 15 of the POLE gene, results from a deletion of one nucleotide at nucleotide position 1478, causing a translational frameshift with a predicted alternate stop codon (p.L493Rfs*13). This alteration is expected to result in loss of function by premature protein truncation or nonsense-mediated mRNA decay. However, loss of function via haploinsufficiency in POLE has not been clearly established as a mechanism of disease. Since supporting evidence is limited at this time, the clinical significance of this alteration remains unclear.</Comment>
